Doc,
sorry to hear it was a hard ride home from Naturalbus--did you change 
the center pivot bushings?? whether you did or not, check the BOLT that 
tightens the swing lever to the center pin.  mine was slightly loose(!) 
causing the symptoms you describe. . . I found this (easy fix) as I was 
in the midst of changing the bushings (challenging fix). there is a lock 
tab that is supposed to prevent this bolt from moving.

Someone (Karl? George?) posted the entire steering box 
centering/adjusting procedure a few months ago and I wasn't able to find 
it in the updated archives.  I am trying to find it because I need to do 
it myself.  below is what I found--folks please comment.  Good luck 
Steve on your project, sounds like it is coming along, it was nice to 
meet you at Everybus (just as you were leaving). and you Doc as well.

happy busin,
